<p><b>The Everly Brothers</b> were American <a href="/wiki/Country_music" title="Country music">country</a>-influenced <a href="/wiki/Rock_and_roll" title="Rock and roll">rock and roll</a> singers, known for <a href="/wiki/Steel-string_guitar" title="Steel-string guitar" class="mw-redirect">steel-string guitar</a> and <a href="/wiki/Close_harmony" title="Close harmony" class="mw-redirect">close harmony</a> singing. Isaac Donald "Don" Everly (born February 1, 1937) and Phillip "Phil" Everly (January 19, 1939 – January 3, 2014) were elected to the <a href="/wiki/Rock_and_Roll_Hall_of_Fame" title="Rock and Roll Hall of Fame">Rock and Roll Hall of Fame</a> in 1986 and the <a href="/wiki/Country_Music_Hall_of_Fame_and_Museum" title="Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum">Country Music Hall of Fame</a> in 2001.</p>
<p></p>
